The paper discusses the use of batch normalization in deep neural networks, which is a common technique in machine learning and falls under the category of deep learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the effects of batch normalization on image classification tasks (cs.CV) and the optimization of neural networks (cs.NE). Additionally, the paper discusses the potential benefits of batch normalization for natural language processing tasks (cs.AI) and the analysis of gradients in deep neural networks (cs.CL).
